# =============================================================================
# Title:   Exercise 3.2 — Reification approach 4: RDF-star
# Purpose: Same fact using RDF-star syntax (<<subject predicate object>> as
#          a quoted triple that can itself be the subject of other triples).
#          Requires RDF 1.2 / RDF-star support (Jena 4.x, Oxigraph, GraphDB).
#          Turtle 1.2 / RDF-star syntax — not all tools support this yet.
# Date:    2026-06-03
# Author:  Barbara Hidalgo-Sotelo (Sensemaking AI)
# =============================================================================

@prefix rdf:         <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs:        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd:         <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix dcterms:     <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
@prefix naruto:      <https://sensemaking-ai.com/ns/naruto#> .
@prefix sensemaking: <https://sensemaking-ai.com/ns/> .

# ── The base facts ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
naruto:ItachiUchiha naruto:killedClan     naruto:UchihaClan .
naruto:ItachiUchiha naruto:actedUnderOrders naruto:DanzoShimura .

# ── RDF-star annotation of the first fact ────────────────────────────────────
# <<subject predicate object>> creates a "quoted triple" that can be used
# as the subject of further triples. This annotates the triple directly
# without a separate node or class.

<<naruto:ItachiUchiha naruto:killedClan naruto:UchihaClan>>
    dcterms:source         "Naruto manga, vol. 43, ch. 401"^^xsd:string ;
    dcterms:date           "2007-05-14"^^xsd:date ;
    sensemaking:confidence sensemaking:CanonicalManga ;
    rdfs:comment           "Revealed in ch. 401 — motivation retconned from personal ambition to Konoha sacrifice."@en .

# ── RDF-star annotation of the second fact ───────────────────────────────────
<<naruto:ItachiUchiha naruto:actedUnderOrders naruto:DanzoShimura>>
    dcterms:source         "Naruto manga, vol. 43, ch. 401"^^xsd:string ;
    dcterms:date           "2007-05-14"^^xsd:date ;
    sensemaking:confidence sensemaking:CanonicalManga .

# ── The earlier, contradictory assertion ─────────────────────────────────────
# The same triple (Itachi killedClan UchihaClan) can appear twice with
# different annotations — once with the ch. 401 source, once with the
# ch. 131 source. This is the key capability: the triple itself is reused;
# only the annotation changes.

<<naruto:ItachiUchiha naruto:killedClan naruto:UchihaClan>>
    dcterms:source         "Naruto manga, vol. 15, ch. 131"^^xsd:string ;
    dcterms:date           "2002-06-03"^^xsd:date ;
    sensemaking:confidence sensemaking:CanonicalDisputed ;
    rdfs:comment           "Early-series portrayal — motivation stated as personal ambition."@en .

# ── Querying RDF-star ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# In SPARQL-star (the query extension), the << >> syntax works in patterns:
#
# SELECT ?source ?confidence WHERE {
#   << naruto:ItachiUchiha naruto:killedClan naruto:UchihaClan >>
#       dcterms:source ?source ;
#       sensemaking:confidence ?confidence .
# }
# ORDER BY ?date
#
# This is more readable than classical reification — you don't have to
# reconstruct the subject/predicate/object to find the annotation nodes.

# ── Advantage and limitation ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Advantage: the cleanest syntax. No intermediate node required. The annotation
# attaches directly to the quoted triple. Queries are readable.
# Limitation: support is not universal (2026). Standard Jena, Oxigraph, and
# GraphDB support it; older Fuseki 3.x and some cloud triplestores do not.
# Before using RDF-star in production, verify your stack supports SPARQL-star
# queries (not just loading the Turtle syntax).
